# [[good for you]]
#: {{syn|fr|[[tant mieux]] [[pour]] [[vous]]}}

====Usage notes====
* Chiefly used [[ironically]], to suggest that the preceding fact is uninteresting or futile.
* Also used in the second- and third-person singular and plural: {{m|fr|grand bien vous fasse}}, {{m|fr|grand bien lui fasse||much good may it do him/her}}, {{m|fr|grand bien leur fasse||much good may it do them}}.
